dict.string: P2 promoter in agr operon from S. aureus
Promoter veg a constitutive promoter for B. subtilis
PliaG is the promoter of the liaG gene of Bacillus subtilis, which is weak and constitutive.
PlepA is the promoter of the lepA gene of Bacillus subtilis. It is a constitutive promoter and does not contain a ribosome binding site.
Pveg is a strong, constitutive promoter of Bacillus subtilis.
The T7 promoter should only produce PoPS when the T7 polymerase is also being expressed.
